{"title_page": "Constituency LA-30", "text_new": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type= Provincial Assembly\n|name=Constituency LA-30 (Jammu and Others-I)\n|year=\n|abolished=\n|parl_name= [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]]\n|member= Nasir Hussain Dar ([[Pakistan Muslim League (N)|PML (N)]])\n|image=File:LA-30 Azad Kashmir Assembly map.png\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region_label=Province\n|province=[[Azad Kashmir]]\n|district=[[Sindh]] [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]] and [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]](except [[Gujranwala Division]] and [[Rawalpindi Division]])\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=26,198\n|previous=\n|next=\n}}\n'''LA-30''' is a constituency of [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]] which is currently represented by Mustafa Bashir Khan of [[Pakistan Muslim League (N)]]. It covers the area of [[Sindh]] [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]] and [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] (except [[Gujranwala Division]] and [[Rawalpindi Division]]) in [[Pakistan]]. Only refugees from [[Jammu Division|Jammu]] and [[Ladakh]] settled in Pakistan are eligible to vote.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electionpakistani.com/azad-kashmir/LA-30.html|title=LA 29 Leepa Hattian Bala AJK Election Result 2016|website=www.electionpakistani.com|access-date=2019-09-02}}</ref>\n==Election 2016==\n{{Further|Azad Kashmir Election 2016}}\nelections were held in this constituency on 21 July 2016.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/|title=ECP - Election Commission of Pakistan|website=www.ecp.gov.pk|accessdate=19 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808103453/https://www.ecp.gov.pk/|archive-date=2018-08-08|url-status=live}} </ref>\n{{Election box begin |title=[[Azad Kashmir Election 2016]]: LA-30 (Jammu and Others-II)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/mobile/folders/1N__F60FsbJrsAA7s0G6Tww8ALhW-fiPo/1SWlmxNtzYkM_YWysh-rt9Ga46j_bnRQW/1ysQ9KU6IIUcH0RmrX3fyfGpdNbIdnaxC?usp=sharing&sort=13&direction=a|title=National Assembly - Google Drive|author=|date=|websi