didate  = Muhammad Nadeem\n|votes      = 5\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n|party      = Independent politician\n|candidate  = Muhammad Aamir Jaral\n|votes      = 3\n|percentage = \n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n|votes      = 9,875\n|percentage =\n|change     = \n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n\n\n\n{{Pakistan-gov-stub}}\n<references />\n[[Category:Government of Azad Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Constituencies of Pakistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox constituency\n|type= Provincial Assembly\n|name=Constituency LA-30 (Jammu and Others-I)\n|year=\n|abolished=\n|parl_name= [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]]\n|member= Nasir Hussain Dar ([[Pakistan Muslim League (N)|PML (N)]])\n|image=File:LA-30 Azad Kashmir Assembly map.png\n|map1=\n|map2=\n|map3=\n|region_label=Province\n|province=[[Azad Kashmir]]\n|district=[[Sindh]] [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]] and [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]](except [[Gujranwala Division]] and [[Rawalpindi Division]])\n|elects_howmany=\n|electorate=26,198\n|previous=\n|next=\n}}\n'''LA-30''' is a constituency of [[Azad Kashmir Legislative Assembly]] which is currently represented by Mustafa Bashir Khan of [[Pakistan Muslim League (N)]]. It covers the area of [[Sindh]] [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]] and [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] (except [[Gujranwala Division]] and [[Rawalpindi Division]]) in [[Pakistan]]. Only refuges from [[Jammu Division|Jammu]] and [[Ladakh]] settled in Pakistan are eligible to vote.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electionpakistani.com/azad-kashmir/LA-30.html|title=LA 29 Leepa Hattian Bala AJK Election Result 2016|website=www.electionpakistani.com|access-date=2019-09-02}}</ref>\n==Election 2016==\n{{Further|Azad Kashmir Election 2016}}\nelections were held in this constituency on 21 July 2016.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/|title=ECP - Election Commission of Pakistan|website=www.ecp.gov.pk|accessdate=19 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.o